      "id": "8d3cb3de_642f720d",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "message": "I have see two different date and timestamp on output:\n\nPlease see below: The git plugin showing the right date and time (as per my local build time) whereas the other (I think spring-boot plugin) showing 1 hour before.\n\nMaybe, we can only have the plugin offered by git, and never use the spring-boot's one.\n\nOtherwise, this may be confusing in the future.\n\n{\n    \"git\": {\n         ...\n        \"build\": {\n            \"time\": \"2024-10-17T10:00:29+01:00\",\n            \"version\": \"3.5.4-SNAPSHOT\"\n        }\n    },\n    \"build\": {\n        \"artifact\": \"cps-application\",\n        \"name\": \"cps-application\",\n        \"time\": \"2024-10-17T08:59:40.724Z\",\n        \"version\": \"3.5.4-SNAPSHOT\",\n        \"group\": \"org.onap.cps\"\n    }\n}",
      "author": {
